Like all facets, //Aptitudes// are measured in dice. They have a maximum rank of 5, and while it is possible to have 0 in a given aptitude, generally all characters will have be at least rank 1 in each. 

When initially making a character select one //Aptititude// as //Primary// and two //Aptititudes// as //Secondary//. The //Primary Aptitude// begins at //Rank// 3, the //Secondary Aptititudes// at //Rank// 2, and the three remaining //Aptititudes// at //Rank// 1.

//Aptitudes// are advanced by spending //Experience//. It costs the square of the rank to be gained to advance, making them costly to increase to higher levels. See the table for more details.

